            <title>[MJAVADOC-110] sourcepath element is not working</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-110</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The attached zip demonstrates the problem.  It is a parent project that has one component.  Just execute &quot;mvn package&quot; in the parent and you will get a File Not Found exception from the javadoc plugin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached the javadoc plugin to the package step, and am using the &amp;lt;sourcepath&amp;gt; element to configure it to look in the subcomponent to get the source files.  This works in 2.0, but fails in 2.1 and 2.2.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I know, I can use &amp;lt;aggregate&amp;gt; instead in this case, but I have other uses cases for &amp;lt;sourcepath&amp;gt; and this is just a simple example to demonstrate the problem.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
